<inglise> Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2134/81 of 28 July 1981 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1105/68 on detailed rules for granting aid for skimmed milk for use as feed </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2134/81, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1105/68 s&ouml;&ouml;dana kasutatavale l&otilde;ssile toetuse andmise &uuml;ksikasjalike eeskirjade kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 28. juuli 1981 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 804/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in milk and milk products (1), as last amended by the Act of Accession of Greece, and in particular Article 10 (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 804/68 piima- ja piimatooteturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud Kreeka &uuml;hinemisaktiga, eriti selle artikli 10 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 5a of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1105/68 (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1645/78 (3), provides for specific rules for granting aid when a dairy uses skimmed milk from its own production exclusively to feed its own animals; whereas it seems justified to provide for the same treatment in cases where the dairy makes its stabling available to a third party who there employs all the skimmed milk produced by the dairy to feed his animals; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1105/68, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1645/78, artiklis 5a on ette n&auml;htud toetuse andmise erieeskirjad juhul, kui meierei kasutab omatoodetud l&otilde;ssi ainult oma loomade s&ouml;&ouml;dana; on &otilde;igustatud n&auml;ha ette samasugune k&auml;sitlemine juhul, kui meierei annab oma loomalaudad kolmanda isiku k&auml;sutusse, kes kasutab meierei toodetud l&otilde;ssi oma loomade s&ouml;&ouml;dana; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, at the same time, an error in the German text of Regulation (EEC) No 1105/68 should be corrected; </inglise>
<eesti> seoses sellega tuleb parandada viga m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1105/68 saksakeelses tekstis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Milk and Milk Products, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las piima- ja piimatooteturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following subparagraph is hereby added to Article 5a (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1105/68: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lisatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1105/68 artikli 5a l&otilde;ikele 1 j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: </eesti>
<inglise> "Animals which a third party keeps in the dairy's buildings and for feeding which the said third party employs, under a contractual arrangement, all the skimmed milk produced in the dairy, shall be treated in the same way as the dairy's own animals." </inglise>
<eesti> Loomi, keda kolmas isik peab meierei hoonetes ja kelle s&ouml;&ouml;tmiseks k&otilde;nesolev kolmas isik kasutab vastavalt lepingulisele kokkuleppele meiereis toodetud l&otilde;ssi, k&auml;sitletakse meierei oma loomadega samav&auml;&auml;rsetena." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> In the German version of Regulation (EEC) No 1105/68, the expression "Artikel 4 bis 8" in Article 1 (9) is hereby replaced by the expression "Abs&auml;tze 4 bis 8". </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1105/68 saksakeelse teksti artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 9 asendatakse s&otilde;nad "Artikel 4 bis 8" s&otilde;nadega "Abs&auml;tze 4 bis 8". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
